org.apache.ignite.streamer.window

Class StreamerBoundedSizeWindow<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ignite.streamer.window.StreamerWindowAdapter<E>
      • org.apache.ignite.streamer.window.StreamerBoundedSizeWindow<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, LifecycleAware, StreamerWindow<E>, StreamerWindowMBean

    public class StreamerBoundedSizeWindow<E>
extends StreamerWindowAdapter<E>
    Queue window bounded by number of elements in queue. After adding elements to this window called must check for evicted events.

    It is guaranteed that window size will never get less then maximum size when poling from this window concurrently from different threads.
